      "id": 224295,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "@ashketchum noticed that we changed our program policy to accept rich text editor-based XSS vulnerabilities and immediately got to testing. What they found was that an attacker could achieve stored XSS by putting a payload directly into the HTML editor and saving the contents, storing malicious code to be executed on subsequent page loads.",
